Riaz Mansoori

 attended 

 in Jan,2016
					
 posted on 27 Jan, 2016

					""Its an highly disciplined institute where there are certain prerequisites for students before they join. they'll have to bring their own chair to sit, own PC or laptop or else access PC in turns, find a place with faculty to teach on your own, One system(PC) per faculty no matter how much students he/she is teaching. He often says hands-on experience, by that he actually means Hands on your lap because all the students gather around one monitor WATCH what faculty is teaching. Its actually an advertising agency with course demonstration in the form of slides and snap shots in the name of teaching. people who themselves don't have job or about to retire work as faculty over here. On the name of course completion certificate which he calls as internship certificate, you'll be given a A4 size printout on xerox paper. In the name of class notes you'll be asked to get it on your own expense by coordinating with faculty. Classes is like train coaches with upper and lower berth and one common filthy bathroom reserved for faculty. Your importance will depend on your fee's payment. if there is delay in payment you will not be allowed to enter classes. you'll be charged per day like a lodge. your batch timing will get gradually replaced by  new batches or with the time that he wakes up. If a faculty asks for white board and marker to teach he suggests to use Microsoft-paint.  After Experiencing all this you must be thinking at least there will be some placement assistance that he promised. but you are wrong here again. After course completion you no longer will be remembered. if you call for placement status you will be flooded with excuses and trials or you'll be asked to watch your tone. After few months you will realize that all your money and time has been wasted. He'll try to play around with you by talking about students being placed but those are ages old. He keeps on changing his classes location so that to get fresh students to cheat. 
A bitter lesson learned, wish I could turn back time. but for others better be safe than sorry.
									""', u'L

 attended 

 in Aug,2015
					
 posted on 31 Aug, 2015

					""The teaching at Bhavani Madame classes was not only educative but the interactive session made me very well versed as to how to appear for the CMA Inter and Final exams. This made me confident for appearing for so called tough exams. Madame is not only very good tutor but an excellent mentor too. The environment she creates in the class was very conducive to bring out the latent talent, which I believe is there in every individual in some form of the other. She is open to new ideas and always ready to solve all queries. 

Just to give a back ground, I am an Engineer and working in Information technology services. I realized that after spending few years  in corporate life, its desire to have overall process view and knowledge of accounting ,costing and Indirect taxes especially when you are working in a consulting area. So I decided to peruse CMA .Now the question was in mind ? where to start? ? from fundamentals like debit and credit ? When I had all these doubts in mind, I came across Bhavani Madame. After I had a brief talk with her about my background, she  encouraged to me to peruse my dream. It is only because of her continuous encouragement which constantly motivated me to work towards my dream. Madame has played a instrumental role in acquiring CMA degree. It has been a great experience.

To sum up, every student works hard to get CMA/CA or another professional degree .The key point is, the teaching and mentoring you have undergone which helps you to face the volatile situation of exams. A dedicated and disciplined student would do well anywhere ? but Bhavani Madame helps to bring out the best in each student and that's the key differentiator.

Lastly, to all aspirants, whether it is CMA title or another dream, dreaming has five stages (according to Sir RB Savella): First is finding the dream. In our childhood days, we think of what we will become when we grow up. Second: Testing it. We go to school to learn how to do it. Third: Fulfilling that dream. We get to work to make it a reality. Fourth: Improving it. We seek continuing learning and growth. Fifth: Sharing the dream. We inspire others.
Thank You!
Regards,
Shishir Rai.
									""', u'R

					""Here is a small composition for TGPC as a thanking gift: Beautiful things happen to a select few Dear TGPC, one of those things happened to me so far, is YOU. You have taught me how to dream and how to work hard in a team You taught me to persevere till end things that messed up u helped me mend. You gave me beautiful teachers whom one can never forget They are the rarest gems on the earth they are the best, you bet! I assure this virtue will always inhabit! 									""', u'S

					""""As I look back I realize that joining TGPC has been one of the best decisions I have ever made.  attended 

 in Oct,2013
					
 posted on 24 Jan, 2016

					""""The learning experience at TGPC was fabulous. Starting from the first lecture of one of the senior sir, I understood that hard work is the only key of success at TGPC. But in all those situations my self motivation helped me a lot. All the faculties along with supporting staff were very much helpful. It was there co-operation and guidance that helped me to achieve good score. But the story did not end there. After that the faculty did so much hard work to train us . They found out the weak points in me and improved it considerably. It was their hard work that led to my selection. Before joining TGPC, I was very shy person. Also my communication skills were very poor. TGPC has made me a mentally strong person who can find ways in any tough situations. Also my communication skills have improved considerably.Specially I am very much thankful to R.K sir for his enormous support and guidance. I have no words to thank TGPC for changing my entire life. I have studied at various classes from my childhood but TGPC is the best and it will remain best. Thank You TGPC..!! ""

Mahesh Engineer

 attended 

 posted on 10 Oct, 2016

					""I joined Harshad Sir for training in ESKRIMA from June 2016. Though I was on the lookout for a martial Arts Trainer for a long time, the comfort with the many Tutors I came across was not in place. It was a luck by chance that I saw his article in the newspaper of being awarded 3rd DAN in ESKRIMA. Harshad Sir is a very dedicated and grounded person. He is practical in approach, patient and very supportive. In the 4 months that I am training under him, I am feeling physically fit and more agile, mentally at peace as he also introduces Yoga exercise to calm down after the Eskrima workouts. I suffer from High BP but this regime under Harshad Sir really has helped me being at peace. I have also lost some excess fat and feel much energetic than before. I would never have done JAL NETI and NETRA NETI on my own but Harshad Sir's presence made me do it very easily and have repeated it many times since. I find both these techniques very beneficial. He is also very knowledgeable in Yoga. I strongly recommend Harshad Sir to all those who want to learn Yoga, Boxing, Kick boxing, Eskrima. Attend his class for just a month and you will feel it's worth it.
									""', u'D

 attended 

 in Jan,2015
					
 posted on 07 Apr, 2016

					""I have had the opportunity to study under Simrit maam for my 2 core subjects; Organisational Theory as well as Core Management Concepts. (U.O.L)
I would describe her teaching style as more friendly and cooperative. She comes down at the student's level and solves each problem. She will not make you feel awkward if you don't know the meaning of an obvious word. 
She instills interpersonal qualities, which helps her identify your strength and weaknesses. 
Above all she knows her knowledge well. She knows what she is talking about and gives you a pre-set framework for your journey through the subject. Later helps you fill up on the framework.
However she does draw a line between spoon feeding and relative independence. She forces you to think harder, which indeed makes your learning’s rock solid and permanent.""']"

column5:
Hindi",Tajmahal,Mumbai,India,400001,"Looking at my school teachers , from early days I was always keen to understand what skills are required to be a GOOD teacher. This curiosity led me to experiment and start teaching since I was in class XI . Although the classes weren't held in professional manner that time but i learnt many things which have helped me understand different mindsets of people and how different words/actions/objects motivate different people to accomplish any task. I have been teaching for 4 years. The best part that I love about is that I get the ability to make a positive and big difference in someone's life and while teaching , I myself learn a lot from the students. My teaching style varies from course to course and person to person. I focus more on the process rather than on xyz targets. I believe in positive motivation and inspiring people to achieve their pre-determined goals. I tell students to interact as teaching is 2-way process.I love each and every subject that i expertise because every subject is beautiful and useful in its own way. I have taught in NGOs , schools and coaching classes and realised the importance of education. I have come to the understanding that we all are into  a program which i call as '' LIFE LONG LEARNING PROGRAM "" . I was awarded the best upcoming teacher in my school. I use power point presentations , printed and hand written notes and believe in e-based learning. Pradnyesh  Bhagat

 attended 

 in Jan,2015
					
 posted on 02 Dec, 2015

					""Namaskar!!! First of all I am not at all capable to write something about such a respectful academy. But still I am writing here because I want to say Thanks to Naadbramha Sangeet Kalamanch.
I joined Naadbramha before a year after inspiring by their one of the stage concert which they performed at Bhakti Gyan Marg Sadhan Santha, Dahisar East on the occasion of Datta Jayanti. I impressed on their team of artist like Flue Player, Tabla, Pakhawaz and hosting of programme(Nivedan) etc... Really it was good set.
Especially, I listened Nilesh Sir in that concert which was memorable for me forever. He is having sweet melodious voice. God has gifted him this quality of voice to sing devotional songs. He performed Raag-Bhimpalasi, Raag-Kalavati, Raag- Puriya, Raag- Malkauns and Raag- Bhairavi etc. I was just connected with god while listening his singing. He is a really versatile singer of Kirana Gharana. Anybody can find same concert on YOUTUBE by putting his name. 
Nilesh Sir is a Chairperson of Naadbramha Sangeet Kalamanch and he directs all  the activities of Naadbramha.  He teach Vocal Classical by own with keeping lot of patience and dedication while teaching to fresh disciples also. Even though this is not Bread n Butter for him. He is highly qualified and working with leading MNC on very senior position.  
I learnt so many things about vocal music under his guidance. I attended his lot of concerts  till date. Especially, one thing I liked about Naadbramha is that everybody is working in Team. All disciples are dedicated for one responsibility at least. They learn, deserve and enjoy while learning Music. 
Finally, Naadbramha is simply awesome. I left few months back because I migrated in Canada for Job but I will never forget all these Naadbramha Days.
Heartiest Thanks to Dearest Nilesh Sir.. Thanks to Naadbramha...
									""', u'D

Karthik

 attended 

 in Dec,2014
					
 posted on 18 Dec, 2014

					""Today I am proud of myself while representing as a most senior student of Naadbramha.I remember that day on which I was taken admission in Naadbramha. Nilesh Sir was not ready to give me admission after listening my such a rude voice. After my humble request he allowed me to be with him but not as a disciple. But I decided to give him company and service during his events and concerts. I used to lift instruments while travelling for any concert. After few months he taught me to set Tanpura.That was my real entry in Naadbramha as a Disciple of Nilesh Sir.I was so happy on that day. After six months he started to teach me Sargam. I started practice honestly but my voice was so heavy. But within a year he modulated my voice and brought me up to the learning level. Today I have completed 9 years in Naadbramha.Till date I am learning classing singing under him. I think this birth will not be enough to grasp even one percent talent of Nilesh Sir.Today I can proudly say that I am the disciple of Raigad Bhushan-Sangeet Visharad Mr. Nilesh Mhatre. He is graded artist of Mumbai Akashwani and Doordarshan. He give me opportunity to sing with him in concerts which is my real receipt of his satisfaction what I have learnt since last 9 years. 

Actually, I am not liable to speak about such a respected person like Nilesh Sir.But I want to speak about his some special qualities. By qualification he is BE (Mechanical Engineering) + MBA (Operations Management) and steering the entire India Operations of leading MNC as a Operations Head. He has struggled well to learn classical music. Being a human being, he is a very royal person and very cooperative nature he has. Really inspirational personality and possesses polite nature.His family is also too good. Sir treat me as a family member only. He balances his professional, musical and family life very well.

Nilesh Sir is good classical vocalist. He sing Khyal, Bandish, Folk, Semi-Classical, Abhangas  Natyageet etc. God has gifted him such a devotional melodious voice hence devotional songs are specialty of his singing. He is quit young, dynamic and energetic artist.

There are lot of albums published in a market in his voice. Narayani Namostute is a super duper hit title of the same.I suggest everybody to have an opportunity to learn music by Nilesh Sir and have a blessings of such a successful person. His teaching method is very friendly and effective.

So join Naadbramha  and be a star of music world within a year.. 

Thanks to Naadbramha.Thanks to Nilesh Sir.
									""']"

column5: English",Andheri Railway Station,Mumbai,India,400058,"When I was in the 9th grade while all my friends were struggling with the choices they had about their chosen field I was 100% sure of what I wanted to study. Psychology is less of a subject and more of home coming for me. I took to the subject like fish to water and although at school level I was always moderately average, at collage level I was topping. Consequently doing my masters was not a big surprise. But my passion for the subject did not end there. I was intrigued with consumer psychology and research methods and since at that time there was no direct course that offered an understanding for both I decided to pursue them separately finishing a Diploma, A second masters and a Certificate program to get all my skills in place. Then I worked for 8 years as a research executive in a market research organisation and then led a successful business for 8 years. Then there was some dormant phase when other duties took priority. Recently a cousins daughter has taken the same liking and was finding the collage teachers teaching method very dry and boring. When she asked me if I would teach her,  I jumped at the proposal and have been teaching her and her friends since the last few months. Teaching them made me realize just how passionate I am about this subject.  So I am now ready to get back to my first love. I would love to teach this subject at all levels from 11th grade onward. I am confident of my compatibility in handling all aspects of the subject.",[],"['BA Tuition', 'Class XI-XII Tuition (PUC)']",https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tv-prod/member/photo/2559746-medium190.jpeg,[]

					""I studied in Eurofluent Language Institute for my pre-admissions preparation in Germany. Aliona was my instructor for German language classes there and I could not have asked for anyone else. Inspite of her having a long experience in teaching in German university she knows the best way to teach it to a complete newbee right from the basics. Akash Choudhary

 attended 

 in Apr,2015
					
 posted on 16 Mar, 2016

					""I might not be good at writing blogs/ articles, but I think I will be able to pen down a lot of good things that happened to me while learning German with Mrs Grama. It all started with my plan to go to Germany for my higher education (Master of Business Administration). I took a demo class from 2 teachers, one was so terrible as compared to the other that I had to go with the other one, the one by Mrs Grama, which I think was the best decision. You don`t just get to learn German, you learn a lot about Germany as well, since she has spent a lot of time there. She is flexible with timings and gives equal opportunity to everyone in her class to learn. I would definitely recommend everyone to join her classes. Danke sehr Frau Grama. Ich hoffe dass wir uns wiedersehen. ""']"

					""Trishika Udyawar, 12th Arts, ?The influence of MIRRA Beautiful Life Class on me.............. Improvement in Drawing Skills & Designing Sense....... improved Imagination....... Personality Development especially Positive Attitude....... Confidence level increased....... Improvement of Listening Skills....... Building up of Good Values like Promptness, Discipline, Best from Waste....... Health benefits with Yog & Meditation....... Better Concentration with Omkar, Dyan Mudra...... Relaxation of Body & Mind with Positive Commands listening..................... I had joined MIRRA Life Class 6 years ago when I was in 6th Std and continued till 7th Summer Vacation. My main objective to join this class was to improve my Drawing as due to Drawing my Grades were suffering. In MIRRA Life Class not only did I improve my Drawing but my Personality Development also. So my overall Grades became better. Very fulfilling experience during my one and half year....... Prof Mohaan Sir conducted ?Exam Preparation Complimentary Workshop? for 10th Students & their Parents and Mirra Mam promptly invited us. I was participant with my Dadee. Great enriching experience of two and half hours with minute details.....................  Then I joined our MIRRA Life Class in June 2015 to get guidance for passing Elementary Grade Drawing Exam. I am very happy that I have been well prepared and have successfully given the Exam. We students are gifted with Tulasi Plants and explained about their Spiritual, Environmental & Medicinal benefits. We are also gifted with laminated prints of Paintings by Prof Mohaan Sir & Nirmitee Mam on special occasions like Birthdays and Success in Exam ................... MIRRA Life Class had a great impact on my personality as well. I enjoyed all sessions like Omkar Chanting, Positive Commands Listening, Imagination Exercise, Public Speaking, Career Guidance, Computer Viewing for Creative Thinking, Demonstration & Discussion and Event Writing. Prof Mohaan Sir & Mirra Mam motivated, guided and helped for my Holistic Growth. I am sure it will be of immense value for rest of my life. I am very happy, fortunate and grateful to be student of MIRRA Life Class, Est in 2003...?
									""', u'P

					""I am very glad that my my daughter Palomy Vival Xavier started attending MIRRA Life Class since October 2013, she began with drawing with std. V.     Firstly, I did a rigorous search on line & got to know of MIRRA Life Classes. When contacted, they appeared to be humble and approachable. More over both the faculty ( Sir & Madam) came across to me as images of grandparents whom my daughter misses as they live in Goa. So, I knew my child was in the right hands of Love and Care. Ever since there has been a great improvement in her Drawing, Colouring, Designing, Imagination, Thought Process and Ideologies towards Life, Discipline, Creativity, Spirituality, Avoiding waste, Behaviours, Minimising Vices & Responsibilities.
 My child was weak in Hindi and Marathi as well, the faculty has taken owness in improving her, in this aspect as well, so much so, that her class teacher mentioned her's was the most neatest paper out of the lot.
There is a lot of area of improvement in my child however, with the thorough guidance and firm support of the awesome faculties, I am sure, my child is on the right track and in the right direction of the beautiful journey of life under the right guidance of the right mentors""', u'S












Shraddha Raorane

 attended 

 in Jan,2012
					
 posted on 11 Apr, 2014

					""Hi, I am Shraddha ! I have graduated in Graphic Design from Sophia Polytechnic in 2011. I have joined MIRRA Life Class in Jan 2012 by recommendation from my friend. Since I am working in Ad Agency as Visualizer I have taken Sunday Batch. ------------ MIRRA Life Class was established in 2003 as Art & Creativity Class. Soon its motto became Personality Enhancement through Art. It is conducted by Mirra Mam and directed by Prof Mohaan Sir. Sir began his career 1973 as Graphic Designer. Today Mohaan Sir is very senior person in field of Design, Creativity and Life? Mirra Mam is the woman behind his success since their marriage in 1979. ------------ I am proud to be student of MIRRA Life Class for last two years. I am very much grateful to Mohaan Sir and Mirra mam for my enrichment in Design, Creativity and Life? Whole ambience of MIRRA Life Class is Positive, Enthusiastic , Confident, Persistent, and Lively ! Sir and Mam have designed their every session in such a way that student from KG to PG are benefitted at their respective level. ------------ I have learnt   and cultivated some beautiful concepts at MIRRA Life Class? For example (1) ?As Fellow your 3 Pillars are Family, Faculty & Friend?? (2) ?Kam Ram Hai?? (3) ?Seer Salamat To Pagadee Pachas??  (4) ?Luck favours the Brave?? (5) ?Mummy Khana Kaise Pakatee Hai ? Dhyanase Aur Pyarase? Hame Padhai Kaisee Karanee Chahiye ? Dhyanase Aur Pyarase?? ------------ I am very lucky to be student of MIRRA Life Class ! It?s just beautiful beginning for me? Towards the long long journey of Life? Wonderful, Peaceful and Blissful? Moment by Moment? Day by Day? Enlightened by Mohaan Sir and Mirra Mam?s guidance? with their Love & Blessings?  I wish them All The Best?
									""', u'S












Srujan Raorane

 attended 

 in May,2004
					
 posted on 03 Apr, 2014

					""Hi, UrbanPro.com?I am Srujan, working as Senior Art Director with an Ad Agency in Mumbai. I have joined MIRRA Life Class in 2003 when it began in Andheri East area. That time I was studying Graphic Design at L. S. Raheja School of Art, Bandra. Soon I will be completing 11 years at MIRRA Life Class. During this span I have learnt many precious things of Life as under :

SUCCESS FORMULA: Mirra Mam conducts MIRRA Life Class which is directed by Prof Mohaan Sir. I graduated in 2005 so for initial two years I got guidance from Sir and Mam to be better student for my college education. Mohaan Sir always tells us about 3H Formula for Success i.e. ?H?ard Work, ?H?ead Work, ?H?eart Work !!! After graduation I have used the formula for beginning and then growth of my career. Now am using it for my Life?
         
COMMUNICATION SKILLS: Mohhan Sir was invited by L. S. Raheja School of Art, Worli as Viva Examiner during 2001-2005. Sir realised that vernacular medium students lack power of expression in English. And incidentally it is ?The Language? of Advertising Field? I have done my S.S.C. in Marathi medium so Mohaan Sir always encouraged me to speak in English? At MIRRA Life Class once in a month we have a brief Public Speaking session where every student has to participate. This certainly boosted my confidence?
         
CREATIVE THINKING: Mohaan Sir receives ?Creative Ideas? from his students who are professionals now. Sir shows these on computer to the students. We all observe, discuss and try to say some thing. Then Sir elaborates and we jot down? At our class we play a game called ?Imagination Exercise? which is similar to ?Tangram? ? the famous Chinese game. We are encouraged to try new things. Both these interesting activities enriched my ?Creative Thinking? which is a must for Advertising Professional !
         
BETTER LIFE: After graduation I have happily continued with MIRRA Life Class as I have benefited with their many activities for Better Life? Mohaan Sir and Mirra Mam?s definition of Better Life is Happiness, Health, Success, Wealth and Long Life? We all students are very lucky to groom ourselves on these aspects by Sir and Mam. Every session begins with Omkar Chanting, Prayer and listening to Positive Commands recorded in Sir?s kind, assuring & soothing voice? Later the recording is given to us in our cellphone so we can listen at home also? Listen More? Benefit More? 
       
GURU ACTIVITY: Mohaan Sir has designed a greeting card for ?GuRu Pournima?. Here the meaning of GuRu is beautifully illustrated, Gu is Darkness? Ru is Light? GuRu takes us from Darkness to Light? We all students are very much grateful to Mohaan Sir and Mirra Mam? for our Wonderful, Beautiful and Blissful Journey from Darkness to Light? We all salute with Devotion Sir and Mam?
									""']"
